"After a violent judicial persecution - carried out with the complicity of certain information and duration 22 years - that has seen me accused in three trials, in which I have always been acquitted, I thought I could spend in peace what little remains of my life." Thus Mario&nbsp;Mori, former deputy commander of the Ros and head of civil intelligence services, in a note in which he informs of having received from the prosecutor of the Republic of Florence, a guarantee notice for the attacks of 1993.
