For the judges of Palermo, argomenta&nbsp;Mori, I was moved exclusively "by solidarity purposes (the safeguard of the domestic collective's safety) and of protection of a general and fundamental interest of the State". Today "I'm being investigated for not stopping the massacres, so with a 360-degree turn compared to the previous theorem. I am deeply disgusted - says&nbsp;Mori&nbsp;- by such accusations that offend, even before my person, the serious magistrates with which I proficuously worked during my career in contrast to terrorism and mafia, on all Giovanni Falcone and Paolo Borsellino. Maybe you don't forgive me for not making their tragic end. Having observed that - the general denounces - the media circle has already started, preceding with a few days before such judicial communication, and being too trivial to assume that the media and judicial aggression will continue with even greater virulence, it seems to me that it is me, and not others, to inform the institutions and public opinion. After that, I'm going to deal with it, and I'm going to get over this new yearning." The instructive act, confirms, "was set for the next 23 May (day of the 32nd anniversary of the massacre of Capaci, ndr) but probably will be postponed since my defender has communicated to the prosecutor of Florence not to be present for concomitant professional engagements in Palermo". &nbsp;

